f:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Rytr is best suited for budget conscious writers, short copy, emails, social media, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. ShortlyAI, meanwhile, shines for blog posts, long form articles, stories, distraction free writing, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2021, Rytr describes itself as \"Budget-friendly AI writing assistant with 40+ use cases.\" ShortlyAI, established in 2020, positions itself as \"Distraction-free AI writing tool focused on long-form content.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
10:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Rytr** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (6.0 vs 5.0), more features (9 vs 2), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean ShortlyAI is a poor choice — far from it. ShortlyAI excels in its own right, particularly for blog posts and long form articles.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value very affordable with unlimited plan at $9/mo, go with Rytr. If clean distraction-free interface matters more to you, ShortlyAI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
